# Allowlist for `claude` CLI invocations inside synced shell scripts.
#
# Each entry pins the bytes of one `# claude-cli-invocations:start` /
# `:end` region. The lint at `.claude/lint-claude-cli-invocations.py`
# computes the sha256 of the bytes between each marker pair and refuses
# to pass if the hash isn't listed here — so any change to the locked
# region must also update this file, and the resulting diff is the
# audit trail for the reviewer.
#
# Format (whitespace-separated):
#   <sha256>  <description>
#
# The description is informational; only the hash is checked.

0d44727f8dab1f2a1cac4d8b81867ca970210d72b78cd57f754287c8e1ff7c0d  agent-loop.sh: spawn claude with bypassPermissions + consumer-owned prompt
